---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
import { LAKES, freshLakes } from '../lib/lakes';
import { breadcrumbLd } from '../lib/seo';

const liveCount = freshLakes().length;
const title = 'About: the developer behind LakeLevelNow';
const description = 'LakeLevelNow is built solo by the independent developer behind zovo.one. Live US lake and reservoir levels from USGS and CDEC. Free, fast, no ads.';
const ld = [breadcrumbLd([{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'About', path: '/about' }])];
const ZOVO = 'https://zovo.one';
const GH = 'https://github.com/theluckystrike';
const EMAIL = 'support@zovo.one';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/about" jsonLd={ld}>
  <div class="container">
    <style>
      .eyebrow{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--teal);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;margin-bottom:18px}
      .about-stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px;margin-top:36px}
      @media(max-width:760px){.about-stats{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
      .about-stats .s{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px}
      .about-stats .s .n{font-size:30px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-.03em;color:var(--ink);font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}
      .about-stats .s .t{font-size:12px;color:var(--t3);margin-top:5px}
      .about-stats .tagline{grid-column:1/-1;font-size:13px;color:var(--t2);font-weight:500;margin-bottom:2px}
      .about-prose p{font-size:15.5px;color:var(--t2);line-height:1.75;max-width:660px}
      .pricing{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:12px;margin-top:8px}
      @media(max-width:760px){.pricing{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
      .price{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);padding:26px;display:flex;flex-direction:column}
      .price.featured{border-color:var(--teal);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px var(--teal-bg)}
      .price .tier{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--t3);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.07em}
      .price .amt{font-size:34px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-.03em;color:var(--ink);margin-top:6px;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}
      .price .amt small{font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:var(--t3);letter-spacing:0}
      .price .blurb{font-size:14px;color:var(--t2);line-height:1.6;margin-top:10px}
      .price ul{list-style:none;padding:0;margin:14px 0 0}
      .price li{position:relative;padding:6px 0 6px 22px;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--t2);border-top:1px solid var(--border-soft)}
      .price li:before{content:"";position:absolute;left:0;top:13px;width:11px;height:6px;border-left:2px solid var(--teal);border-bottom:2px solid var(--teal);transform:rotate(-45deg)}
      .price .btn{margin-top:18px;text-align:center}
      .links-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:12px;margin-top:8px}
      @media(max-width:760px){.links-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
      .link-card{display:block;background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px;color:inherit;transition:transform .15s,box-shadow .15s}
      .link-card:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);box-shadow:var(--shadow-hover);text-decoration:none}
      .link-card .lt{font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--ink)}
      .link-card .ld{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--t3);margin-top:5px;line-height:1.5}
      .try-cta{background:var(--ink);border-radius:var(--r);padding:40px;margin-top:8px;color:#fff}
      .try-cta h2{color:#fff;font-size:24px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
      .try-cta p{color:rgba(255,255,255,.7);font-size:15px;max-width:560px;line-height:1.65}
      .try-cta .btn{margin-top:8px;background:#34b8a0;color:#06231d}
      .try-cta .btn:hover{background:#2ea391}
      .section-h{font-size:20px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:10px}
      .section-k{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--teal);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.07em;margin-bottom:4px}
    </style>

    <section class="hero" style="padding-top:56px;">
      <div class="eyebrow">The person behind the tools</div>
      <h1 style="max-width:620px;">About LakeLevelNow</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width:600px;">I'm an independent developer and I build small, fast utility sites. LakeLevelNow is one of them. Check how full a lake is, see a 30-day trend, and get a straight answer on whether you can launch a boat, pulled straight from USGS and CDEC gages. No account, no pop-ups, no essay before the gauge loads.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="about-stats">
      <div class="tagline">Solo. Full-time. Coffee-powered.</div>
      <div class="s"><div class="n">{LAKES.length}</div><div class="t">lakes in the registry</div></div>
      <div class="s"><div class="n">2</div><div class="t">live data feeds (USGS + CDEC)</div></div>
      <div class="s"><div class="n">0</div><div class="t">sign-ups required</div></div>
      <div class="s"><div class="n">0</div><div class="t">ads or pop-ups</div></div>
    </div>

    <section class="section about-prose">
      <div class="section-k">What I build</div>
      <h2 class="section-h">One job per site, done fast</h2>
      <p>Most lake-level sites are scraped tables that haven't been updated since the last flood season, or a single hobbyist page for one reservoir. I went the other way. Every lake pulls its own live gage (<b>USGS</b> for most, <b>CDEC</b> for California reservoirs) so the number you see is the same one the operator reports, stamped with exactly when it was taken.</p>
      <p>The <b>"can I launch?"</b> read turns a raw elevation into the thing you actually wanted to know: will the ramp be in the water this weekend. It's a level-based guide, not a guarantee. Always confirm the ramp with the operator before you go.</p>
      <p>I build the whole site on my own and work on it full time. That's the only reason the data stays fresh and a request for a new lake actually gets read the same day.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section about-prose">
      <div class="section-k">The honest part</div>
      <h2 class="section-h">What's live, and what isn't</h2>
      <p>Not every lake has a real-time gage. Some I wired up and the feed went dark; those show <b>"feed connecting"</b> and reference data, never a made-up number. A reading only counts as live if it's within seven days; anything older gets flagged "may be delayed" rather than passed off as current.</p>
      <p>So I'd rather hear what's wrong than guess at it. Wrong gage, mislabeled lake, a reservoir you'd like added: send it over. Small fixes usually ship the same week, and the bigger ideas go on a list I actually work through.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-k">Support and access</div>
      <h2 class="section-h" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Keep it free, or get all of it</h2>
      <p class="about-prose" style="margin-bottom:20px;">Every page here is free and stays free. There's no paywall on the water level, and there never will be. Two options if you want more than that.</p>
      <div class="pricing">
        <div class="price">
          <div class="tier">Pro · one payment</div>
          <div class="amt">$4.99</div>
          <div class="blurb">A small thank-you for the work. It covers the server bill, pushes your requests up the list, gets you new tools before they go public, and keeps the site ad-free.</div>
          <ul>
            <li>Your feature requests near the top of the queue</li>
            <li>Early access to tools still in testing</li>
            <li>No subscription, nothing to cancel</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn" href={ZOVO} rel="nofollow noopener">Get Pro on zovo.one</a>
        </div>
        <div class="price featured">
          <div class="tier">Lifetime · best value</div>
          <div class="amt">$99 <small>once</small></div>
          <div class="blurb">Every tool I build, for good. The zovo.one lifetime membership covers this site and everything else I make: no monthly fee, no per-tool charge.</div>
          <ul>
            <li>Lifetime access to every tool on zovo.one, now and not-yet-shipped</li>
            <li>The zovo.one Chrome extension and BeLikeNative, included</li>
            <li>Your requests jump the queue · one payment, kept for good</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn" href={ZOVO} rel="nofollow noopener">Get lifetime on zovo.one</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-k">Where everything lives</div>
      <h2 class="section-h" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Tools, code, and a real inbox</h2>
      <p class="about-prose" style="margin-bottom:20px;">The tools, the membership, and the rest of what I make all live on zovo.one. The code I can share sits on GitHub. Got a question before you spend anything? Email me and a real person (me) writes back.</p>
      <div class="links-grid">
        <a class="link-card" href={ZOVO} rel="nofollow noopener"><div class="lt">zovo.one</div><div class="ld">The tools, the membership, and lifetime access in one place.</div></a>
        <a class="link-card" href={GH} rel="nofollow noopener"><div class="lt">GitHub</div><div class="ld">The code I keep in the open, plus what I'm tinkering with. github.com/theluckystrike</div></a>
        <a class="link-card" href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}><div class="lt">Email</div><div class="ld">A feature idea, a bug, or a question before you buy. {EMAIL}</div></a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section try-cta">
      <div class="section-k" style="color:#34b8a0;">Try the tools first</div>
      <h2>The best way to decide is to use the thing</h2>
      <p>Start with a lake you know. Check how full it is and whether you can launch. Come back if you want the rest.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/lakes">Browse the lakes →</a>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
